# Agent control (minimum — always active)

Applies to **Cursor Auto**, Composer, and chat agents in this workspace.

## Before any work

1. Read `artifacts/_index.md` and `artifacts/project_state.json` (even if `empty_project: true`).
2. Read last lines of `artifacts/.changes.jsonl` if it exists.
3. State **which files you will change** and **why** — then wait for user confirmation on large or ambiguous tasks.

## Scope limits

- Edit **only** files required for the stated task.
- **Ask first** before creating new files or new top-level folders.
- Do **not** refactor, lint-fix, or "improve" unrelated code after the task.
- **Stop** when the task is done — do not start the next task unprompted.

## Read-only zones

Never edit: `artifacts/`, `.cursor/rules/`, `CLAUDE.md`.

## Empty project (no source modules yet)

Planning and architecture discussion are allowed. Do not invent a full codebase unless the user asks.
Use `direction` in _index.md when set. Remind: "Add code when ready, then ⟳ Refresh."

## After code changes

Tell the user: "Click **⟳ Refresh** to update artifacts." Do not run refresh unless asked.
